          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I feel like that I took a right decision to make my child to be the part of Gurukul (an esteemed educational institute). Herein teaching and non-teaching staff is very supportive and open to any suggestion. Teaching strategies adopted by teachers seems to be an amalgamation of traditional and modern ways (such as inclusion of online methods to make teaching session more fun) to make kids understand the basics of their studies in more lucid way. Not only this but also, it’s a great relief as a parent when we see that school administration provides extra care to our children as an when required, which satisfies me a lot. Apart for focusing on kids for their education, school administration equally works on school and parent connect. Time to time they make programs full of fun and learning activities, wherein kids, parents and teaching staff participates. In such environment parents also feel connected with their kid’s schools. One more thing which I personally like about Gurukul is the transparency they provide to the parents, be it academics, extracurricular part or related to any policy/rule mentioned by the school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
